olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
20 g butter
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup water
1 packet couscous
1 packet Apricot Sauce
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Grate carrot. Thinly slice courgette into half moons.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging. In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, chermoula spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt.

• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil and the butter over medium-high heat.
• Cook courgette until tender, 2-3 minutes. Add carrot and cook until softened, 2-3 minutes.
• Add chicken-style stock powder and the water, and bring to the boil. Add couscous, then stir to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside until the water has absorbed, 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Return all beef to the pan and remove pan from heat. Add apricot sauce and a splash of water and toss beef to coat.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender

• Add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil to the couscous. Generously season with salt and pepper and stir to combine.
• Divide veggie couscous between bowls.
• Top with sticky Moroccan beef and Greek style yoghurt. Enjoy!